Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #medium bowl{}, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g}, @chermoula spice mix{1%portion}, garlic, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and @zhoug style paste{1%tbsp} and @Greek style natural yoghurt{1%tbsp}.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix together well.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the marinated chicken to the pan. Discard any remaining marinade.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Meanwhile, pop the tomatoes into a medium bowl. Season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch}.

Drizzle in some @olive oil{drizzle}.

Toss together, then set aside.

Sprinkle the @plain naans{2} with a little water and pop them into the #oven{} to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to the tomatoes. Toss to coat.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the remaining @zhoug style paste{1%tbsp} and @Greek style natural yoghurt{1%tbsp}.

When everything is ready, share the naans between your plates.

Top with the chermoula chicken, tomatoes and rocket.

Drizzle over the zhoug yoghurt to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook the recipe in the same way.